<p>the mounted troops are leaving this front &amp; that we are going to Yudia for garrison duty. Certainly most of the yeomanry have gone down to Deir El Belah. But I think all this retrograde movement <strike>has a great deal to do</strike> is largely due to the difficulties of transporting fodder when we have so many divisions of infantry in front of us as well.</p>
<p>This is a very sedentary life here now, the sick &amp; ailing usually keep us working in the morning</p>
